title: La princesse du Nil
overview: Neteb, Princess of Egypt, is depicted as the younger sister of Queen Nefertari and the sister-in-law of Pharaoh Ramesses II (reigned 1279-1213 BCE). Neteb is an amateur detective, typically investigating domestic conspiracies against Ramesses. She also helps in cases involving foreign enemies, such as rogue Hittite princes. Neteb is also a student of medicine, and her medical training often saves the lives of crime victims.
